Colour.
Basal colour black (Fig. 

). Clypeus tricolourous, with black border, brown basally attached median spot nearly reaching apex, yellowish-white laterally (Fig. 

). Smaller yellowish spot adjacent to inner orbit, reddish-yellow interantennal area, mandible whitish with brown tip and blackish basal area (Figs 

, 

). Scape dark brown dorsally, ferruginous ventrally (Fig. 

). Flagellum dorsally blackish, ventrally reddish, with several distal segments orange ventrally (Fig. 

). Pronotum with thin yellow line underneath carina (Fig. 

), scutellum faint reddish postero-laterally, metanotum with two large yellow spots occupying two thirds of total surface, propodeum entirely black (Fig. 

). Legs black, femora with thin reddish line on inner side; tarsi somewhat darker. Wings infuscated, with moderate darkening in tip of basal cell and majority of marginal cell (Fig. 

). T1 with reddish-yellow triangular mark laterally (Fig. 

). T2 with complete posterior yellow band, S2 with partial posterior band (interrupted medially); remaining terga and sterna black.
